1 AN ACT concerning technical colleges; establishing the Kansas technical
2 college operating grant fund administered by the state board of regents.
3
4 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
5 Section 1. (a) There is hereby established in the state treasury the
6 Kansas technical college operating grant fund, which shall be administered
7 by the state board of regents. All expenditures from the Kansas technical
8 college operating grant fund shall be for instruction and operations to meet
9 target objectives established by the postsecondary technical education
10 authority for each technical college's region and the entire state. All
11 expenditures from the Kansas technical college operating grant fund shall
12 be made in accordance with appropriation acts upon warrants of the
13 director of accounts and reports issued pursuant to vouchers approved by
14 the executive officer of the state board of regents or the executive officer's
15 designee.
16 (b) As used in this section, "technical college" means the same as
17 defined in K.S.A. 71-1802, and amendments thereto, and the Washburn
18 institute of technology
19 Sec. 2. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
20 publication in the statute book Kansas register.

